# Client-side vulnerabilities 

## Check for sensitive data exposure 
  - Right click on web page -> Select View page source. 
  - Identify any low-hanging fruits such as credentials, hashes, or other sensitive data in comments of the source code. Other valuable information include exposed links, directories, 
  user information, debugging parameters, hidden functionalities, etc. 
  HTML comments use this syntax: <--! comment -->

## Check for HTML injection 
- Identify input fields such as a search box, a login form, a signup form, a contact form, a comment section, etc. 
- Inject basic payloads using different types of tags. Check whether your input was processed as HTML code or not. 

